fields.description:
Create Agent class that wraps a pi AgentSession.

## Deliverables
- src/agent/worker.ts

## Design
```typescript
class Agent {
  readonly id: AgentId;
  readonly type: string;
  readonly depth: number;

  private session: AgentSession;
  private status$: BehaviorSubject<Status>;
  private structuredOutput?: unknown;

  constructor(options: AgentOptions);

  prompt(message: string): Promise<string>;  // submission_id
  interrupt(): Promise<void>;
  shutdown(): Promise<void>;

  get status(): Status;
  subscribeStatus(): Observable<Status>;
}
```

## Key Behaviors
- Wraps pi-coding-agent's createAgentSession
- Status updates on session events (turn_start → running, turn_complete → completed, etc.)
- Handles structured output via submit_result tool injection
- tool_choice forced to 'any' when result_schema provided
- Skills injected into system prompt

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Creates AgentSession with resolved policy (model, tools, thinking)
- [ ] Status observable emits on state changes
- [ ] prompt() sends user message, returns submission_id
- [ ] interrupt() aborts current streaming
- [ ] shutdown() cleanly terminates session
- [ ] Structured output captured when submit_result called
- [ ] tool_choice='any' when result_schema provided
- [ ] Skills injected into system prompt
- [ ] Sandbox config clamped to parent's config
- [ ] Depth tracked from parent
